		<Vehicles.VehicleBuildDef ParentName="VehicleBaseBuildable">
			<defName>GF40K_RhinoBluePrint</defName>
			<label>Rhino</label>
			<description>The Rhino armored personnel carrier is one of the most common armored vehicles in the Imperium of Man. It is favored due to its durability and versatility. Rhino is easy to construct and can be modified for different tasks, becoming a platform for mounting additional weapons, although this may limit the number of personnel it can carry.\nCommonly used by the Space Marines, it is also used by the Adeptus Mechanicus, Adepta Sororitas, Legio Custodes and Inquisition.\nA single driver controls the Rhino, simultaneously managing the remotely operated Storm Bolter. The suppressive fire it provides, in addition to the smoke screens, enables safe deployment of personnel. The engines of the Rhino are a remarkable feat of engineering, able to operate on almost any variety of flammable fuel. In the event of an engine malfunction during a battle, the remaining engine will sustain movement of the APC across the battlefield.\n\n&lt;color=#ffd75d&gt;Crew:&lt;/color&gt; Driver x1, Personnel x6\n&lt;color=#ffd75d&gt;Armament: &lt;/color&gt;Storm Bolter,\nSmoke Launcher\n&lt;color=#ffd75d&gt;Fuel type:&lt;/color&gt; Chemfuel</description>
			<graphicData>
				<texPath>Things/Vehicles/Rhino/rhino</texPath>
				<graphicClass>Graphic_Multi</graphicClass>
				<drawSize>(5,5)</drawSize>
			</graphicData>
			
			<size>(5,5)</size>
			<statBases>
				<MaxHitPoints>1200</MaxHitPoints>
				<WorkToBuild>15500</WorkToBuild>
				<Flammability>0.1</Flammability>
			</statBases>
			
			<researchPrerequisites>
				<li>GF40K_RhinoBaseResearch</li>
			</researchPrerequisites>
			<constructionSkillPrerequisite>6</constructionSkillPrerequisite>

			<costList>
				<Steel>600</Steel>
				<Plasteel>100</Plasteel>
				<ComponentIndustrial>18</ComponentIndustrial>
			</costList>

			<designationCategory>VF_Vehicles</designationCategory>
			<soundImpactDefault>BulletImpact_Metal</soundImpactDefault>
			<soundBuilt/>
			<thingToSpawn>GF40K_Rhino</thingToSpawn>
		</Vehicles.VehicleBuildDef>

		
